document_data.History:
Warren I assumed the throne of the High King in [[Callidyrr]] after the death of his father in the {{YearlinkName|250}}. He was thirteen years old, and at the same time, [[Cedric Riker]] was made regent in the family's original seat at [[Corwell]].{{Cite dragon/362/Grand History of the Realms: The Moonshaes|26}}

In the [[256 DR|sixth year of his reign]], [[Illuskan]] raiders from [[Tuern]] and [[Gundarlun]] arrived in the Moonshaes and laid claim to the northernmost islands, which the Ffolk were forced to concede. This marked the beginning of the long struggle between the Ffolk and the [[Northmen]], and the start of seasonal raids on the southern islands.

Warren I ruled for nine years before dying of [[disease|illness]] in the {{YearlinkName|259}}. Regent Riker would continue to hold his position throughout the young king's entire reign.
